OL,6,FHer overpayment of #1623 occurred
OL,7,Fbecause she thought that earnings
OL,8,Fwould be averaged over the year, for
OL,9,Fexample she wasn't working during the
OL,10,Fsummer holidays. She took it a
OL,11,Ftribunal, but the Judge ordered her to
OL,12,Fpay it back in full which she did.
OL,14,F"It made me feel like a criminal,"
OL,15,Fsaid Tait. "If you a carer, you are
OL,16,Funder immense strain and you're not
OL,17,Falways on top of your finances as at
OL,18,Fthat particular point."
