OL,6,FBeing a supply teacher, she said, you
OL,7,F"quite often you get asked to do more
OL,8,Fwork and I would just wanted to pay
OL,9,Fthe bills and I inadvertently went
OL,10,Fover the limit."
OL,12,FThe CEO of Carers UK said that the
OL,13,Fhours for the working threshold should
OL,14,Fbe increased to 21 hours of the
OL,15,Fnational living wage.
OL,17,FThis, Helen Walker says, would "cut
OL,18,Fout that cliff edge, if they go over
OL,19,Fby just a pound, it would be tapered."
